	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001286_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Pearl - Mersey</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"> 10<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> March </p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1858 </p>
<lb/><p>Dear <persName>Sir George</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I have always 
<lb/>been sorry that 
<lb/>I failed to respond 
<lb/>to your polite 
<lb/>attentions in 
<lb/>person, but though 
<lb/>I scarcely deserve 
<lb/>your forgiveness 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001286_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'-->
<lb/>I hope you will 
<lb/>allow me to explain 
<lb/>that I have been 
<lb/>for a long time 
<lb/>in a very unnatural 
<lb/>state and it will 
<lb/>be only when 
<lb/>I get away into 
<lb/>the quiet for 
<lb/>which I long 
<lb/>that I shall be 
<lb/>able to pay those 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001286_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'-->
<lb/>attentions to my 
<lb/>friends which 
<lb/>they assuredly 
<lb/>merit. We are 
<lb/>now fairly started 
<lb/>having lifted the 
<lb/>anchor at 1 P.M. 
<lb/>today. We are 
<lb/>well and well 
<lb/>provided for<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>The launch a 
<lb/>photograph of 
<lb/>which will be 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001286_0004"/><!--pb/@n='2v'-->
<lb/>sent you is safely 
<lb/>stowed in three 
<lb/>pieces on deck 
<lb/>and we hope 
<lb/>that by God's 
<lb/>help &amp; blessing 
<lb/>we shall make 
<lb/>a good use of 
<lb/>her. Our kindest 
<lb/>salutations to 
<lb/><persName>Lady Back</persName><reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am &amp;c </p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
			
</div>
